This codebase is mounted through **nyne**, a FUSE virtual filesystem. Every source file has an `@/` companion directory exposing tree-sitter-decomposed symbols, LSP code actions and intelligence, git history, and more.

**All `@/` paths are real files** — they work with the Read tool, Edit tool, Write tool, Bash commands, and shell pipes.

The nyne VFS enables efficient, targeted and precise code traversal, access and modification, with minimal token consumption. **Using nyne is always more efficient and effective than accessing raw source files.** Always use the nyne VFS and companion files in `@/` for code exploration, analysis, and edits — raw source files should only be accessed as a last resort.
